<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.51/993: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-28T10:00:00-06:00">May 28,
                                    1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>282. My 279, May 27, 5 p.m. obviously crossed the Department’s No. 207,
                            May 27, 2 p.m. I propose therefore if the Department approves <pb facs="0263" n="249" xml:id="pg_249"/> to withhold action on the
                            Department’s 207 until the Department has an opportunity to comment on
                            my 279.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>